{"blocks":[{"key":"12m8g","text":"Check the correct box on the screen for the objective magnification. Click OK. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":69,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a8hiv","text":"No software prompt is needed to install the flow cell. {"blocks":[{"key":"1k1ks","text":"Screw the black tubing piece (lower silicone tubing denoted in Figure 2C, Step 6) into the bottom of the flow cell. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":116,"length":65}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e37mo","text":"Carefully fit the beige tubing piece into the top of the sample inlet port (Figure 2D) and tighten. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7f7o6","text":"Carefully position the tubing into the fluid position sensor (black fitting under the sample port inlet) and position the flow cell into the flow cell retainer cavity underneath, ensuring it is not scratched. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bmonf","text":"Insert the flow cell retainer piece gently into the cavity with the flow cell until it is flush with the rest of the cavity, and gently tighten thumb screws (if you overtighten, they will smash or scratch flow cell.) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":129,"length":14},{"style":"bold","offset":156,"length":61}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eltgp","text":"Ensure the face of the flow cell (with the etching at the top) is facing toward you. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6rgpe","text":"Take the tubing end of the lower silicone tubing (Figure 2E) and fit it over the syringe port. Ensure tubing is sitting straight and not twisted or scrunched. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":95,"length":64}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bd35b","text":"Click Set-up and then select pump. Select change flow cell and turn the plunger lock screw counterclockwise three times. Press OK. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":12},{"style":"bold","offset":29,"length":4},{"style":"bold","offset":42,"length":16},{"style":"bold","offset":121,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6ele8","text":"The plunger will be pulled down by the syringe pump. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cha8u","text":"Turn the syringe counterclockwise and remove it. Press OK. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":49,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4m1ld","text":"Screw in a new syringe and pull down the plunger so it is centered flush with the syringe pump. Press OK. The Syringe arm will push the plunger up into the syringe. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":96,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"db14u","text":"Tighten the plunger screw-lock on the syringe arm by turning clockwise and press OK. Select the size of the syringe installed and press OK. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":75,"length":8},{"style":"bold","offset":130,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8h7ds","text":"Ensure the cleaner and rinse receptacles are full of 2% citra-jet and Milli-Q respectively. Empty the waste receptacle. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4s3om","text":"Cleaning is recommended prior to every use and immediately after.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2dbi","text":"Open the FlowCam software (visual spreadsheet) and select set-up, pump, and make sure the correct syringe size is listed in the syringe size box. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":51,"length":15}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"87ppe","text":"Click the “Clean/Rinse” button. {"blocks":[{"key":"5to5e","text":"Select the “Setup/Focus” button at top of the screen. A live view of the camera will appear, along with a pump control box.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":25}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9d0so","text":"The red lines (acceptable region) indicate the area that will be imaged. Adjust the red lines to be just inside the edges of the flow cell. Generally, cultures were run as is if at a \"low density\" (under ~5 million cells per mL), or diluted 1:4 media (e.g., ASP12A) to culture. ASP12A media preparation is defined in the protocol linked below. ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b5eq8","text":"Following set-up of the FlowCam by manufacturer's instructions (using the 20✕ objective, 20✕ flow cells, and 0.5 or 1.0 mL syringe; green set) and the full clearance of Milli-Q water through the tubing, enter the flow cell view mode (i.e., \"Camera View\"), apply at least 500 μL of your sample, and start the flow at 1–2 mL/minute. Once cells appear within the on screen camera aim at the flow cell, halt the manual priming (close the window). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":234,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"88uvh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8gf8h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6tbvu","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"a257q","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"5ukna","text":"The 20✕ objective scheme permits a maximum particle size of 50 μm, an AutoImage rate range of 20 to 84 frames per second, and an efficiency range of 33.0 to 99.7%. {"blocks":[{"key":"3f35v","text":"Cell image capture (and subsequent descriptive statistics) is processed via the AutoImage mode. Simply click the auto image mode, set the acquisition method constraints, provide a sample name/ID, and initiate the sampling.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5qjon","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"54etr","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"8gjfp","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":656,"offset":0,"style":"italic"}],"key":"9hn0e","text":"For statistically significant results set the number of cells measured accordingly. Most in-lab cultures will be dense enough to achieve at least 5000–10 000 cell photos. It is possible to reach up to 35 000 (or more) photos in highly dense cultures. Environmental samples will likely possess much fewer cells and may require several addition steps, including pre-filtering to accommodate the size limitation of a 20✕ objective set-up and determining the sample volume required to reach statistically significant results (i.e., enough A. anophagefferens images captured). Environmental studies of A. anophagefferens are outside the scope of this protocol. ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
